net.varkhan.base.containers.queue
Class BoundedHeapFloatQueue

java.lang.Object
  net.varkhan.base.containers.queue.BoundedHeapFloatQueue
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.lang.Iterable, Container<java.lang.Float>, FloatQueue, Queue<java.lang.Float>, FloatVisitable, Visitable<java.lang.Float>
public class BoundedHeapFloatQueue
extends java.lang.Object
implements FloatQueue

A heap-based bounded priority queue containing floats.

This class uses a fixed-size heap to provide the semantics of a priority queue on floats, using either ascending or descending order.

When the size of the queue equals the maximum size bound (the size of the heap), adding an element triggers the discarding of the smallest element in the queue (which could be the added element).
